**Dashboard Outline**

Goal: provide a dashboard of results to outsiders. 

* Data to be initially inputted manually; other data values to be calculated automatically based on the inputted data  
* Assume inputted data may need to be changed later  
* Data \= simple profit or loss amount or percentage. No data regarding the number of trades, time of trade, direction of trade, kind of trade (e.g., call/put), etc.   
* Later: we will want to turn off and on certain ways of viewing the data (see below for more about this)

1. Required views

   

   1. User sees his account summary:  
      1. ![][image1]  
         1. Before we open this page to outsiders, I can input the   
            1. First and last name of the account   
            2. “beginning value”.  
            3. “Change”  
         2. Then, you should automatically calculate the   
            1. % change  
            2. current value 

      

   2. User also sees the daily returns for the current month  
      1. ![][image2]  
         1. I would like to input the percentage with as many decimals as I would like and that should be used to calculate the other values in the Account Summary section. However, we should only show one decimal.  
         2. The “month’s current return” is simply the current cumulative (running) return for the month.

      

   3. After I input the daily % gain/loss value (after market close), the following should get updated in the Account Summary section:  
      1. Change   
      2. % change  
      3. Current value 

      

   4. There will be multiple users who will have their own view. They will have different names and “beginning value” values in their account summary. But ideally, when one daily % gain/loss is updated, it should get updated in other user accounts. If not automatically done, then I can manually go into each account and input the daily % gain/loss  
        
   5. We will need to have the correct dates for each month for the table  
      1. We will include listing half-day trading sessions  
      2. Should use the trading calendar program Eric is using but here are the trading days for the rest of the year  
         1. October (every weekday): 1-3; 6-10; 13-17; 20-24; 27-31  
         2. November: 3-7; 10-14; 17-21; 24-26 (no 27); 28th is a half day that closes at 1pm ET    
         3. December: 1-5; 8-12; 15-19; 22-23, 24th is a half day; (no 25), 26; 29-31

   

2. Login

   

   1. username: we assign to them or they create?  
        
   2. password: we assign to them or they create?   
      1. if they create the username, then they would create the password.   
      2. We would then need to support the “forgot password” process

   

3. Note: manual input of data that is noted above; assume data that was manually inputted may need to be changed later  
     
4. Other data sets that may be supported later on:

   

   1. Past monthly returns but not including the current month  
      1. ![][image3]

      

   2. Multi-time periods from the past  
      1. ![][image4]  
         1. YTD \= Year to Date, i.e., the return for the current year from Jan 1st to the current date

      

   3. May add other tables or charts later  
        
   4. Should design these data sets so we can choose which views to turn on or off depending on what we want to share. If we share one view to one user, other users would see the same type of view
